om%2Fremote-work-from-home-return-to-office-americans-employment-wfh-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egolden%20ticket%20of%20WFH%20gigs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20can%20seem%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconcert-tickets-price-taylor-swift-economics-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eharder%20to%20snag%20than%20seats%20at%20a%20Taylor%20Swift%20concert%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20are%20just%20some%20jobs%20Americans%20won't%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20aren't%20much%20of%20a%20surprise%3A%20fast-food%20worker%2C%20trash%20collector%2C%20and%20cashier.%20Others%2C%20like%20pharmacy%20tech%2C%20restaurant%20host%2C%20or%20working%20the%20front%20desk%20at%20a%20hotel%2C%20might%20seem%20like%20a%20step%20up%2C%20but%20they're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhardest-roles-employers-fill-uk-social-workers-credit-controllers-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eamong%20the%20hardest-to-fill%20jobs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20about%20the%20green%3A%20If%20you%20want%20to%20work%20as%20a%20merchandiser%2C%20where%20the%20average%20advertised%20salary%20is%20about%20%2475%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20Adzuna%2C%20you'd%20practically%20have%20your%20pick%20of%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGen%20Zers%20want%20to%20see%20what's%20next%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20reason%20these%20jobs%20could%20be%20hard%20to%20hire%20for%20is%20because%20some%20workers%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20perhaps%20especially%20Gen%20Zers%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0won't%20say%20yes%20to%20a%20role%20that%20doesn't%20have%20an%20obvious%20next%20step%2C%20James%20Neave%2C%20head%20of%20data%20science%20at%20Adzuna%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20really%20prioritize%20things%20like%20flexibility%20and%20career%20growth%20and%20mental-health%20support%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20younger%20workers.%20%26quot%3BIt%20comes%20down%20to%20kind%20of%20broader%20cultural%20shifts%20in%20the%20workforce%20in%20terms%20of%20what%20certain%20demographics%20are%20looking%20for%20in%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20of%20us%2C%20the%20pandemic%20rebooted%20our%20relationship%20with%20work%20and%20how%20much%20we%20want%20to%20give%20over%20to%20our%20employers.%20That%20means%2C%20according%20to%20Neave%2C%20that%20companies%20having%20trouble%20plugging%20people%20into%20open%20jobs%20will%20need%20to%20be%20more%20thoughtful%20about%20what%20they're%20offering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20need%20to%20consider%20whether%20workers%20have%20sufficient%20opportunities%20for%20training%20and%20promotions.%20Workplace%20culture%20and%20things%20like%20benefits%20are%20also%20important%2C%20he%20said.%20So%20is%20pay.%20%26quot%3BSalary%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20the%20big%20lever%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Neave%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWFH%20won't%20necessarily%20attract%20workers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20allowing%20someone%20to%20work%20from%20home%2C%20which%20has%20proven%20so%20attractive%20that%20some%20workers%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foveremployed-remote-jobs-tech-full-time-bosses-work-savings-advice-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ejuggling%20more%20than%20one%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20remote%20role%2C%20isn't%20a%20magic%20fix.%20Customer%20support%20specialists%20in%20work-from-home%20roles%20had%20an%20average%20salary%20of%20nearly%20%2460%2C000%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%2C%20Adzuna%20found.%20But%20job%20seekers%20weren't%20clicking%20away%20on%20those%20listings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20determine%20which%20jobs%20were%20least%20appealing%20to%20applicants%2C%20Adzuna%20reviewed%20job%20titles%20that%20had%20more%20than%2050%20open%20positions%20in%20the%20final%20quarter%20of%202023.%20Some%20jobs%20that%20are%20broadly%20in%20demand%20might%20see%20fewer%20clicks%20per%20ad%20because%20there%20are%20so%20many%20openings%2C%20Neave%20said.%20And%20other%20high-skill%20jobs%20that%20made%20the%20least-popular%20rankings%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0including%20java%20developer%20and%20veterinarian%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0might%20have%20more%20to%20do%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhardest-software-engineering-interviews-ranked-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehow%20such%20roles%20are%20usually%20filled%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThe%20jobs%20come%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Neave%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20software%20developers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20other%20roles%20that%20do%20seem%20genuinely%20hard%20to%20fill%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0think%20sales%20floor%20associate%20or%20hotel%20housekeeper%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0employers%20might%20need%20to%20get%20creative%2C%20Neave%20said.%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20they%20need%20to%20take%20a%20step%20back%20and%20have%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20rethink%20about%20how%20they%20define%20these%20roles%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeave%20said%20building%20in%20more%20responsibilities%20to%20some%20roles%20could%20help%20attract%20people%20who%20want%20more%20than%20just%20a%209-to-5%20gig%20or%20who%20don't%20want%20to%20do%20the%20same%20thing%20every%20day.%20%26quot%3BThat%20has%20been%20what%20many%20millions%20of%20humans%20have%20probably%20done%20for%20thousands%20of%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%2C%20you%20know%2C%20times%20are%20changing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-wfh-jobs-americans-dont-want-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704351841000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6595ac92ec62ab5daf8062ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-wfh-jobs-americans-dont-want-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Work-from-home%20jobs%20are%20often%20hard%20to%20find%20and%20highly%20coveted.%20But%20some%20roles%20are%20so%20unpopular%20they%20don't%20get%20much%20interest%20from%20job%20seekers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-wfh-jobs-americans-dont-want-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20Row%20Over%20PM%20Selfie%20Points%2C%20Indian%20Railways%20Tighten%20RTI%20Norms%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F29112023%2FUntitled-design-16-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EFollowing%20the%20controversy%20over%20the%20cost%20of%20selfie%20points%20with%20Prime%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20image%20installed%20at%20railway%20stations%2C%20the%20Indian%20Railways%20has%20tightened%20norms%20for%20Zonal%20Railways%20furnishing%20information%20under%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20Act.%20As%20per%20the%20changed%20rules%2C%20all%20RTI%20replies%20must%20go%20through%20general%20managers%20of%20zonal%20railways%20or%20divisional%20railway%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Railway%20Board%2C%20in%20an%20advisory%20sent%20out%20to%20general%20managers%2C%20on%20December%2028%2C%202023%2C%20said%20it%20had%20come%20to%20its%20notice%20that%20lately%20%E2%80%9Cquality%20of%20replies%20to%20RTI%20applications%20handled%20by%20Zonal%20Railways%20and%20other%20field%20units%20had%20deteriorated%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Fstriking-fear-on-hit-and-run-accident-cases-and-section-106-of-the-bharatiya-nyaya-sanhita%2Farticle67703190.ece%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTimelines%20for%20disposal%20of%20RTI%20applications%20were%20surpassed%20in%20many%20cases%20resulting%20in%20a%20large%20number%20of%20appeals%20filed%20before%20the%20First%20Appellate%20Authority%20or%20the%20Central%20Information%20Commission%2C%20not%20only%20increasing%20the%20quantum%20of%20work%20but%20bringing%20disrepute%20to%20the%20organisation%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20advisory%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20tide%20over%20these%20problems%2C%20the%20advisory%20said%20a%20decision%20had%20been%20made%20that%20timelines%20for%20disposal%20prescribed%20in%20the%20Act%20should%20be%20complied%20with%20at%20any%20cost.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20it%20also%20said%20to%20ensure%20quality%2C%20all%20RTI%20replies%20going%20forward%20must%20be%20approved%20respectively%20at%20the%20level%20of%20the%20general%20manager%20(GM)%20in%20Zonal%20Railways%20and%20divisional%20railway%20managers%20(DRMs)%20in%20the%20Divisions.%C2%A0%E2%80%9CSimilarly%2C%20replies%20to%20first%20appeals%20received%20under%20the%20RTI%20Act%20need%20to%20be%20shown%20to%20the%20GM%20and%20DRM%20concerned%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20advisory%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20Railways%20had%20Public%20Information%20Officer%20and%20Chief%20Public%20Information%20Officer%20under%20provisions%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%202005%2C%20to%20furnish%20information%20sought%20by%20petitioners.%20Neither%20general%20managers%20nor%20divisional%20railway%20managers%20had%20any%20role%20to%20play%20as%20appellate%20or%20competent%20authority%20as%20per%20the%20Act%2C%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20quoting%20sources%20in%20the%20Southern%20Railway.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20changes%20have%20been%20brought%20into%20force%20after%20it%20came%20to%20light%20that%20each%20permanent%20selfie%20booth%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20image%20costs%20Rs%206.25%20lakh%20while%20each%20temporary%20selfie%20booth%20costs%20Rs%201.25%20lakh%2C%20which%20is%20the%20approved%20cost%20by%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Communication%20under%20Ministry%20of%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting.%20The%20above%20information%20was%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20furnished%20by%20the%20Central%20Railway%20in%20response%20to%20an%20RTI%20query.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20controversy%20further%20deepened%20after%20the%20authorities%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentral-railways-pro-transferred-without-notice-after-releasing-costs-of-modi-selfie-points%5C%22%3Etransferred%3C%2Fa%3E%20Central%20Railway%E2%80%99s%20Public%20Relations%20Officer%20Shivaji%20Manaspure%20against%20the%20backdrop%20that%20it%20was%20Manaspure%E2%80%99s%20deputy%2C%20Abhay%20Mishra%2C%20as%20Deputy%20General%20Manager%20of%20Central%20Railway%2C%20disclosed%20the%20information%20pertaining%20to%20selfie%20points.%20Manaspure%20had%20been%20in%20the%20post%20for%20seven%20months%20while%20the%20tenure%20of%20the%20said%20post%20is%20for%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20sought%20to%20underline%20that%20Manaspure%E2%80%99s%20transfer%20was%20done%20as%20an%20act%20of%20punishment%20due%20to%20the%20embarrassment%20caused%20to%20the%20Modi%20government.%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EShahenshah%20ki%20raza%2C%20sach%20ka%20inaam%20saza%3C%2Fi%3E%20(King%20rewards%20truth%20with%20punishment)%2C%E2%80%9D%20Gandhi%20had%20written%20on%20X%20(formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAuthorities%20at%20Indian%20Railways%20refute%20the%20allegations%20that%20Manaspure%E2%80%99s%20transfer%20was%20due%20to%20the%20information%20revealed%20on%20selfie%20points.%20They%20say%20it%20was%20only%20due%20to%20operational%20reasons.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20they%20say%20revised%20guidelines%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20RTI%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Ajay%20Bose%2C%20a%20former%20railway%20employee%2C%20who%20had%20sought%20information%20on%20selfie%20points%20through%20an%20RTI%20application%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CRTIs%20filed%20to%20seek%20response%20on%20expenditure%20incurred%20%5Bon%20the%203D%20booths%5D%20from%20Southern%2C%20Western%20and%20Northern%20Railways%20did%20not%20elicit%20any%20response.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704351635000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F29112023%2FUntitled-design-16-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fafter-row-over-pm-selfie-points-railways-tightens-rti-norms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20per%20the%20changed%20rules%2C%20all%20RTI%20replies%20from%20Indian%20Railways%20must%20go%20through%20general%20managers%20of%20zonal%20railways%20or%20divisional%20railway%20managers.%20So%20far%2C%20public%20information%20officers%20and%20chief%20public%20information%20officers%20handled%20the%20matter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fafter-row-over-pm-selfie-points-railways-tightens-rti-norms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22RM%20%26amp%3B%20V%20pose%20as%20military%20recruits%20in%20new%20pics%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704351591000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106536972%2Cimgsize-60860.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fk-pop%2Fmusic%2Fnews%2Fbts-rm-v-pose-as-new-recruits-with-fellow-trainees-at-nonsan-training-center%2Farticleshow%2F106536881.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F106536881.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ERM%20and%20V%2C%20members%20of%20BTS%2C%20have%20enlisted%20at%20the%20Korean%20Army%20Training%20Center%20in%20Nonsan.%20New%20pictures%20show%20them%20blending%20in%20with%20fellow%20trainees.%20RM%20proudly%20wears%20a%20blue%20tag%2C%20while%20V%20covers%20the%20lower%20half%20of%20his%20face.%20The%20Nonsan%20Tra