ump-disqualified-from-2024-primary-ballot-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20question%20of%20whether%20he%20can%20be%20barred%20from%20Colorado's%20presidential%20primary%20ballot%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20petition%20filed%20Wednesday%2C%20Trump's%20legal%20team%20urged%20SCOTUS%20to%20overturn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-supreme-court-backs-colorado-take-off-ballot-report-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%204-3%20ruling%20in%20December%20by%20the%20Colorado%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20found%20that%20his%20role%20in%20the%20January%206%2C%202021%2C%20attack%20on%20the%20US%20Capitol%20disqualified%20him%20under%20the%20clause.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWednesday's%20development%20came%20a%20day%20after%20Trump's%20legal%20team%20filed%20an%20appeal%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-ineligible-maines-primary-ballot-secretary-of-state-rules-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20ruling%20by%20Maine's%20Democratic%20Secretary%20of%20State%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Shenna%20Bellows%2C%20that%20Trump%20was%20ineligible%20to%20appear%20on%20that%20state's%20ballot%20over%20his%20role%20in%20the%20Capitol%20attack.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20Colorado%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20Maine%20secretary%20of%20state's%20rulings%20are%20on%20hold%20until%20the%20appeals%20play%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20critics%20have%20filed%20dozens%20of%20lawsuits%20seeking%20to%20disqualify%20him%20in%20multiple%20states.%20He%20lost%20Colorado%20by%2013%20percentage%20points%20in%202020%20and%20does%20not%20need%20to%20win%20the%20state%20to%20gain%20either%20the%20Republican%20presidential%20nomination%20or%20the%20presidency.%20But%20the%20Colorado%20ruling%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20prompt%20courts%20or%20secretaries%20of%20state%20to%20remove%20him%20from%20the%20ballot%20in%20other%2C%20must-win%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20had%20succeeded%20until%20a%20slim%20majority%20of%20Colorado's%20seven%20justices%20%E2%80%94%20all%20appointed%20by%20Democratic%20governors%20%E2%80%94%20ruled%20last%20month%20against%20Trump.%20Critics%20warned%20that%20it%20was%20an%20overreach%20and%20that%20the%20court%20could%20not%20simply%20declare%20that%20the%20Jan.%206%20attack%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Binsurrection%26quot%3B%20without%20a%20judicial%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Colorado%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20would%20unconstitutionally%20disenfranchise%20millions%20of%20voters%20in%20Colorado%20and%20likely%20be%20used%20as%20a%20template%20to%20disenfranchise%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20voters%20nationwide%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump's%20lawyers%20wrote%20in%20their%20appeal%20to%20the%20nation's%20highest%20court%2C%20noting%20that%20Maine%20has%20already%20followed%20Colorado's%20lead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20new%20appeal%20to%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20also%20follows%20one%20from%20Colorado's%20Republican%20Party.%20Legal%20observers%20expect%20the%20high%20court%20will%20take%20the%20case%20because%20it%20concerns%20unsettled%20constitutional%20issues%20that%20go%20to%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20way%20the%20country%20is%20governed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20parties%20to%20the%20case%20have%20urged%20the%20court%20to%20move%20quickly.%20Trump's%20lawyers%20on%20Wednesday%20asked%20the%20court%20to%20overturn%20the%20ruling%20without%20even%20hearing%20oral%20arguments.%20The%20lawyers%20representing%20the%20Colorado%20plaintiffs%20have%20urged%20oral%20arguments%20but%20also%20seek%20a%20vastly%20accelerated%20schedule%2C%20calling%20for%20a%20resolution%20by%20next%20month.%20Colorado's%20primary%20is%20March%205.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESean%20Grimsley%2C%20an%20attorney%20for%20the%20plaintiffs%20seeking%20to%20disqualify%20Trump%20in%20Colorado%2C%20said%20late%20last%20month%20on%20a%20legal%20podcast%20called%20%26quot%3BLaw%2C%20disrupted%26quot%3B%20that%20he%20hopes%20the%20nation's%20highest%20court%20hurries%20once%20it%20accepts%20the%20case%2C%20as%20he%20expects%20it%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20primary%20coming%20up%20on%20Super%20Tuesday%20and%20we%20need%20to%20know%20the%20answer%2C%26quot%3B%20Grimsley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Colorado%20high%20court%20upheld%20a%20finding%20by%20a%20district%20court%20judge%20that%20Jan.%206%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Binsurrection%26quot%3B%20incited%20by%20Trump.%20It%20agreed%20with%20the%20petitioners%2C%20six%20Republican%20and%20unaffiliated%20Colorado%20voters%20whose%20lawsuit%20was%20funded%20by%20a%20Washington-based%20liberal%20group%2C%20that%20Trump%20clearly%20violated%20the%20provision.%20Because%20of%20that%2C%20the%20court%20ruled%20he%20is%20disqualified%20just%20as%20plainly%20as%20if%20he%20failed%20to%20meet%20the%20Constitution's%20minimum%20age%20requirement%20for%20the%20presidency%20of%2035%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20doing%20so%2C%20the%20state%20high%20court%20reversed%20a%20ruling%20by%20the%20lower%20court%20judge%20that%20said%20it%20wasn't%20clear%20that%20Section%203%20was%20meant%20to%20apply%20to%20the%20president.%20That's%20one%20of%20many%20issues%20the%20nation's%20highest%20court%20would%20consider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditional%20ones%20include%20whether%20states%20such%20as%20Colorado%20can%20determine%20who%20is%20covered%20by%20Section%203%2C%20whether%20congressional%20action%20is%20needed%20to%20create%20a%20process%20to%20bar%20people%20from%20office%2C%20whether%20Jan.%206%20met%20the%20legal%20definition%20of%20insurrection%20and%20whether%20Trump%20was%20simply%20engaging%20in%20First%20Amendment%20activity%20that%20day%20or%20is%20responsible%20for%20the%20violent%20attack%2C%20which%20was%20intended%20to%20halt%20certification%20of%20Democrat%20Joe%20Biden's%20victory.%20Trump%20held%20a%20rally%20before%20the%20Capitol%20attack%2C%20telling%20his%20supporters%20that%20%26quot%3Bif%20you%20don't%20fight%20like%20hell%2C%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20have%20a%20country%20anymore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20of%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court's%20nine%20justices%20were%20appointed%20by%20Republicans%2C%20and%20three%20by%20Trump%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Colorado%20ruling%20cited%20a%20prior%20decision%20by%20Neil%20Gorsuch%2C%20one%20of%20Trump's%20appointees%20to%20the%20high%20court%2C%20when%20he%20was%20a%20federal%20judge%20in%20Colorado.%20That%20ruling%20determined%20that%20the%20state%20had%20a%20legitimate%20interest%20in%20removing%20from%20the%20presidential%20ballot%20a%20naturalized%20US%20citizen%20who%20was%20ineligible%20for%20the%20office%20because%20he%20was%20born%20in%20Guyana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESection%203%2C%20however%2C%20has%20barely%20been%20used%20since%20the%20years%20after%20the%20Civil%20War%2C%20when%20it%20kept%20defeated%20Confederates%20from%20returning%20to%20their%20former%20government%20positions.%20The%20two-sentence%20clause%20says%20that%20anyone%20who%20swore%20an%20oath%20to%20%26quot%3Bsupport%26quot%3B%20the%20Constitution%20and%20then%20engaged%20in%20insurrection%20cannot%20hold%20office%20unless%20a%20two-thirds%20vote%20of%20Congress%20allows%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20scholars%20believe%20its%20only%20application%20in%20the%2020th%20century%20was%20being%20cited%20by%20Congress%20in%201919%20to%20block%20the%20seating%20of%20a%20socialist%20who%20opposed%20US%20involvement%20in%20World%20War%20I%20and%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%202022%2C%20a%20judge%20used%20it%20to%20remove%20a%20rural%20New%20Mexico%20county%20commissioner%20from%20office%20after%20he%20was%20convicted%20of%20a%20misdemeanor%20for%20entering%20the%20US%20Capitol%20on%20Jan.%206.%20Liberal%20groups%20sued%20to%20block%20Republican%20Reps.%20Madison%20Cawthorn%20and%20Marjorie%20Taylor%20Greene%20from%20running%20for%20reelection%20because%20of%20their%20roles%20on%20that%20day.%20Cawthorn's%20case%20became%20moot%20when%20he%20lost%20his%20primary%20in%202022%2C%20and%20a%20judge%20ruled%20to%20keep%20Greene%20on%20the%20ballot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20conservatives%20warn%20that%2C%20if%20Trump%20is%20removed%2C%20political%20groups%20will%20routinely%20use%20Section%203%20against%20opponents%20in%20unexpected%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden's%20administration%20has%20noted%20that%20the%20president%20has%20no%20role%20in%20the%20litigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20of%20whether%20Trump%20can%20be%20on%20the%20ballot%20is%20not%20the%20only%20matter%20related%20to%20the%20former%20president%20or%20Jan.%206%20that%20has%20reached%20the%20high%20court.%20The%20justices%20last%20month%20declined%20a%20request%20from%20special%20counsel%20Jack%20Smith%20to%20swiftly%20take%20up%20and%20rule%20on%20Trump's%20claims%20that%20he%20is%20immune%20from%20prosecution%20in%20a%20case%20charging%20him%20with%20plotting%20to%20overturn%20the%20presidential%20election%2C%20though%20the%20issue%20could%20be%20back%20before%20the%20court%20soon%20depending%20on%20the%20ruling%20of%20a%20Washington-based%20appeals%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20court%20has%20said%20that%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fsupreme-court-capitol-riot-obstruction-charge-trump-5cf0db4a71766f0b40ec199dd0d5a1ab%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintends%20to%20hear%20an%20appeal%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20could%20upend%20hundreds%20of%20charges%20stemming%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Fhub%2Fcapitol-siege%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Capitol%20riot%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20against%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-asked-scotus-to-overturn-ban-from-colorado-ballot-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704335631000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659618e4ec62ab5daf808013%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%