22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fgurgaon%2F8-years-after-gangsters-encounter-in-mumbai-hotel-girlfriend-shot-in-gurgaon-hotel%2Farticleshow%2F106527709.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Divya%20Pahuja%2C%20an%20aspiring%20model%2C%20was%20killed%20in%20a%20Gurgaon%20hotel%20allegedly%20by%20the%20hotel%20owner%2C%20in%20what%20police%20describe%20as%20the%20outcome%20of%20a%20blackmail%20plot.%20Divya%20was%20shot%20in%20room%20111%20after%20she%20had%20checked%20into%20the%20hotel%20with%20the%20owner%20at%204.15am.%20The%20murder%20came%20to%20light%20when%20Divya's%20sister%20found%20CCTV%20footage%20showing%20two%20men%20dragging%20the%20body%20wrapped%20in%20a%20bedsheet%20to%20a%20waiting%20BMW%20car.%20Divya%20had%20been%20named%20as%20a%20police%20mole%20in%20the%20charge%20sheet%20filed%20in%20Mumbai%20into%20the%20killing%20of%20Sandeep%20Gadoli%2C%20a%20notorious%20gangster%2C%20by%20the%20Gurgaon%20police.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22BAGISH%20JHA%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Elise%20Stefanik%20took%20credit%20for%20Claudine%20Gay's%20resignation%2C%20but%20it%20was%20in%20large%20part%20due%20to%20a%20Gen%20Z%20reporter%20who%20says%20liberals%20should%20care%20about%20this%20story%20too%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22former%20Harvard%20President%20Claudine%20Gay%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65947514ec62ab5daf801677%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Schiefelbein%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHarvard%20University%20President%20Claudine%20Gay%20resigned%20Tuesday%20after%20months%20of%20controversy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20plagiarism%20accusations%20that%20piled%20up%20against%20Gay%20were%20revealed%20by%20Gen%20Z%20reporter%20Aaron%20Sibarium.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESibarium%20said%20the%20story%20should%20matter%20to%20both%20liberals%20and%20conservatives.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20president%20of%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20prestigious%20universities%20stepped%20down%2C%20an%20opportunistic%20Republican%20lawmaker%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaudine-gay-harvard-resignation-elise-stefanik-fires-shot-elite-colleges-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3ERep.%20Elise%20Stefanik%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20quick%20to%20take%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20will%20always%20deliver%20results%2C%26quot%3B%20Stefanik%20triumphantly%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FRepStefanik%2Fstatus%2F1742256789939204429%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3Etweeted%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20Harvard%20President%20Claudine%20Gay%20announced%20her%20resignation%20on%20Tuesday.%20Stefanik%20pointed%20to%20questions%20she%20asked%20about%20antisemitism%20on%20campus%20during%20a%20hearing%20with%20the%20presidents%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%2C%20Harvard%2C%20and%20MIT.%20The%20answers%20the%20presidents%20gave%20sparked%20bipartisan%20backlash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20far%20more%20credit%20was%20likely%20due%20to%20Aaron%20Sibarium%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Gen%20Z%20reporter%20trying%20to%20bring%20investigative%20journalism%20to%20conservative%20media.%20Sibarium%2C%20a%20writer%20at%20the%20conservative%20news%20site%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffreebeacon.com%2Fauthor%2Faaron-sibarium%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3EThe%20Washington%20Free%20Beacon%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20broke%20many%20of%20the%20plagiarism%20accusations%20against%20Gay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-president-claudine-gay-to-resign-reports-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGay%20resigned%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20months%20of%20controversy%20that%20started%20after%20Hamas%20attacked%20Israel%20on%20October%207%20but%20ramped%20up%20after%20the%20Congressional%20hearing%20last%20month.%20In%20her%20tweet%20taking%20credit%20for%20the%20resignation%2C%20Stefanik%20cited%20Gay's%20%26quot%3Bmorally%20bankrupt%20answers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20the%20criticism%20of%20Gay%20that%20followed%20the%20testimony%2C%20Harvard's%20board%20stood%20by%20her.%20It%20wasn't%20until%20the%20plagiarism%20accusations%20continued%20to%20pile%20up%20that%20she%20resigned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20email%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Sibarium%20said%20he%20pursued%20the%20story%20because%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20public%20interest%20to%20know%20whether%20Harvard%20%E2%80%94%20a%20beacon%20of%20academic%20prestige%20that%20receives%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20in%20federal%20aid%20%E2%80%94%20is%20willing%20to%20tolerate%20serial%20plagiarism%20from%20its%20own%20president%2C%20even%20as%20it%20disciplines%20students%20for%20the%20same%20offense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGay%20appeared%20to%20allude%20to%20the%20allegations%20in%20her%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaudine-gay-harvard-resignation-letter-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3Eresignation%20letter%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20writing%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bdistressing%20to%20have%20doubt%20cast%20on%20my%20commitments%20to%20confronting%20hate%20and%20to%20upholding%20scholarly%20rigor%20%E2%80%94%20two%20bedrock%20values%20that%20are%20fundamental%20to%20who%20I%20am%20%E2%80%94%20and%20frightening%20to%20be%20subjected%20to%20personal%20attacks%20and%20threats%20fueled%20by%20racial%20animus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20reached%20by%20email%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Gay%20declined%20to%20comment%20further.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20op-ed%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F01%2F03%2Fopinion%2Fclaudine-gay-harvard-president.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20Wednesday%2C%20Gay%20strongly%20defended%20her%20scholarship%20but%20acknowledged%20she%20had%20made%20attribution%20mistakes%20and%20requested%20corrections%20in%20the%20relevant%20journals%2C%20which%20she%20said%20was%20consistent%20with%20how%20similar%20faculty%20cases%20had%20been%20handled%20at%20Harvard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20have%20also%20argued%20the%20attacks%20on%20Gay%20were%20made%20in%20bad%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.harvard.edu%2Fblog%2F2024%2F01%2F02%2Fstatement-from-the-harvard-corporation-president-gay%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3EHarvard%20Corporation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20school's%20governing%20body%2C%20said%20in%20a%20separate%20statement%20it%20accepted%20her%20resignation%20with%20%26quot%3Bsorrow%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20Gay%20had%20%26quot%3Backnowledged%20missteps%20and%20has%20taken%20responsibility%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESibarium%2C%20a%2027-year-old%20Yale%20University%20alumnus%20whom%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2Fmagazine%2F2023%2F11%2F25%2Faaron-sibarium-conservative-media-00117899%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3EPolitico%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20profiled%20in%20November%2C%20has%20been%20making%20waves%20in%20conservative%20media%20for%20several%20years.%20But%20his%20author%20page%20shows%20how%20he%20spent%20the%20past%20month%3A%20breaking%20stories%20about%20plagiarism%20accusations%20against%20Gay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20latest%20piece%2C%20published%20Monday%2C%20detailed%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffreebeacon.com%2Fcampus%2Fharvard-president-claudine-gay-hit-with-six-new-charges-of-plagiarism%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3Esix%20new%20allegations%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGay%20resigned%20the%20following%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20Sibarium's%20conservative%20reporting%20chops%2C%20he%20told%20Politico%20that%20he's%20not%20conservative%20himself%20%E2%80%94%20he%20just%20saw%20an%20opening%20and%20a%20need%20for%20legitimate%2C%20traditional%20journalism%20from%20a%20conservative%20perspective.%20(He's%20described%20by%20a%20colleague%20in%20the%20Politico%20piece%20as%20%26quot%3Bliberal%2C%20but.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20the%20Harvard%20students%2C%20liberal%20or%20conservative%2C%20who%20have%20meticulously%20checked%20their%20work%20out%20of%20fear%20of%20missing%20a%20footnote%20or%20those%20who%20have%20actually%20been%20punished%20for%20plagiarizing%20a%20term%20paper%2C%20let%20alone%20a%20dissertation%20or%20peer-reviewed%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20fail%20to%20cite%20your%20sources%2C%20or%20when%20you%20cite%20them%20inadequately%2C%20you%20are%20plagiarizing%2C%20which%20is%20taken%20extremely%20seriously%20at%20Harvard%2C%26quot%3B%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fusingsources.fas.harvard.edu%2Favoiding-plagiarism-0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3Eschool%20warns%20students%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BPlagiarism%20is%20defined%20as%20the%20act%20of%20either%20intentionally%20OR%20unintentionally%20submitting%20work%20that%20was%20written%20by%20someone%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20student%20handbook%20also%20says%3A%20%26quot%3BStudents%20who%2C%20for%20whatever%20reason%2C%20submit%20work%20either%20not%20their%20own%20or%20without%20clear%20attribution%20to%20its%20sources%20will%20be%20subject%20to%20disciplinary%20action%2C%20up%20to%20and%20including%20requirement%20to%20withdraw%20from%20the%20College.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarvard%20also%20notes%20that%20professors%20are%20held%20to%20the%20same%20standards%2C%20telling%20students%3A%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20write%20papers%20in%20college%2C%20your%20work%20is%20held%20to%20the%20same%20standards%20of%20citation%20as%20the%20work%20of%20your%20professors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllegations%20against%20Gay%20range%20from%20inadequate%20citations%20to%20lifting%20nearly%20verbatim%20sections%20of%20copy%20from%20other%20academics'%20papers%20or%20books.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuch%20double%20standards%20are%20relevant%20to%20people%20of%20all%20political%20stripes%20%E2%80%94%20and%20perhaps%20to%20liberals%20most%20of%20all%2C%20since%20they%20are%20the%20ones%20who%20comprise%20the%20lion's%20share%20of%20students%20and%20faculty%20at%20Harvard%2C%26quot%3B%20Sibarium%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20seriousness%20of%20the%20accusations%20against%20Gay%20has%20been%20hotly%20debated%2C%20with%20some%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F12%2F20%2Fbusiness%2Fharvard-president-claudine-gay-plagiarism%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3Eplagiarism%20experts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20calling%20the%20instances%20more%20nuanced%20than%20the%20outrage%20would%20suggest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20some%20scholars%20whom%20Gay%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20plagiarizing%20have%20dismissed%20the%20allegations%2C%20including%20David%20Canon%2C%20a%20political%20science%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Wisconsin%2C%20Madison.%20Gay%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20using%20nearly%20verbatim%20language%20from%20Canon's%201999%20book%20in%20an%20article%20she%20published%20in%202001.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20not%20at%20all%20concerned%20about%20the%20passages%2C%26quot%3B%20Canon%20told%20the%20Washington%20Free%20Beacon%20in%20Sibarium's%20latest%20story.%20%26quot%3BThis%20isn't%20even%20close%20to%20an%20example%20of%20academic%20plagiarism.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Sibarium%20said%20that's%20not%20his%20call%20to%20make.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20can%2C%20of%20course%2C%20debate%20the%20seriousness%20of%20Gay's%20conduct%20and%20whether%20the%20rules%20on%20plagiarism%20are%20too%20strict%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BMy%20job%20as%20a%20reporter%20is%20to%20get%20the%20raw%20examples%20out%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-reporter-aaron-sibarium-harvard-president-claudine-gay-plagiarism-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704326249000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6594c768ab6f2ebb11f8577e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-reporter-aaron-sibarium-harvard-president-claudine-gay-plagiarism-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gen%20Z%20reporter%20Aaron%20Sibarium%20broke%20many%20of%20the%20plagiarism%20accusations%20that%20piled%20up%20against%20Harvard%20President%20Claudine%20Gay%2C%20who%20resigned%20Tuesday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-reporter-aaron-sibarium-harvard-president-claudine-gay-plagiarism-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Britney%20Spears%3A%20%E2%80%98I%20Will%20Never%20Return%20to%20the%20Music%20Industry%E2%80%99%20and%20New%20Album%20Rumors%20Are%20%E2%80%98Trash%E2%80%99%26nbsp%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704325262000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2Fbritneyspears.png%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235860934%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Britney%20Spears%20has%20shut%20down%20the%20rumor%20that%20she%20is%20working%20on%20a%20new%20album%20in%20a%20candid%20Instagram%20post%20where%20she%20brazenly%20declares%20she%20will%20%E2%80%9Cnever%20return%20to%20the%20music%20industry.%E2%80%9D%20The%20pop%20singer%20was%20seemingly%20responding%20to%20reports%20that%20surfaced%20early%20Wednesday%20morning%20on%20Page%20Six%20about%20Spears%20potentially%20tapping%20Charli%20XCX%20and%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22