3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20some%20places%20they%20are%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emallah%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20at%20other%20places%20they%20are%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emachhuara%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eor%20fishermen.%20They%20are%20also%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enishads%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekevat%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20members%20of%20this%20group%20are%20present%20in%20almost%20every%20state%20including%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Odisha%2C%20Assam%2C%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Tripura.%20Famous%20ethnologists%2C%20Russell%20and%20Hira%20Lal%2C%20wrote%20in%20their%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETribes%20and%20Castes%20of%20the%20Central%20Provinces%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1916)%20that%20the%20Kevats%20were%20a%20mixed%20caste.%20They%20highlighted%20that%20this%20caste%20group%20had%20no%20relation%20with%20the%20Aryans%20and%20are%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20original%20natives.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EH.H.%20Risley%20had%20also%20underlined%20in%20his%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETribes%20and%20Castes%20of%20Bengal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1891)%20that%20they%20had%20blood%20ties%20with%20the%20tribals.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20now%20they%20are%20known%20in%20different%20states%20by%20different%20names%20assigned%20to%20them%20recently.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20Chhattisgarh%20they%20are%20known%20as%20Nishad%2C%20Jalchhatri%20and%20Parker.%20In%20Assam%2C%20they%20were%20earlier%20known%20as%20Halwa%20Keot%2C%20but%20nowadays%20members%20of%20this%20caste%20identify%20themselves%20as%20Kevat.%20In%20Bihar%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20they%20are%20known%20as%20Mallah%2C%20Kevat%2C%20Nishad%20and%20Machhuara.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20recent%20caste-based%20census%20report%20released%20by%20the%20Bihar%20government%2C%20the%20population%20of%20the%20Mallah%20caste%20group%20in%20Bihar%20is%203%2C410%2C093%20(2.36085%25%20of%20the%20population)%20and%20that%20of%20Kevat%20caste%20group%20is%20937%2C861%20(0.717%25)%2C%20while%20Kaivart%20caste%20population%20is%20265%2C943%20(0.2034%25)%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20population%20of%20Bind%20caste%20group%20which%20is%201%2C285%2C358%20(0.9833%25).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20we%20look%20at%20the%20combined%20population%20of%20all%20these%20castes%2C%20the%20total%20is%205%2C899%2C255.%20Even%20though%20the%20Kevat%20caste%20group%20has%20a%20sizeable%20share%20in%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20population%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20about%20130%20million%2C%20their%20political%20participation%20is%20negligible.%20All%20these%20caste%20groups%20are%20included%20in%20the%20extremely%20backward%20class%2C%20and%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20they%20are%20marginalised%20not%20only%20in%20politics%20but%20in%20government%20jobs%20too.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20Rajputs%20with%20population%204%2C510%2C733%20and%20Bhumihars%20with%20population%203%2C775%2C885%2C%20both%20of%20whom%20have%20a%20much%20smaller%20population%20than%20the%20total%20population%20of%20the%20Kevat%20caste%20group%2C%20have%20been%20decisive%20in%20the%20political%20arena.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Kevat%20caste%20group%20are%20ones%20who%20helped%20Ram%20cross%20the%20Saryu%20river.%20But%20this%20story%20cannot%20be%20believed%20because%20in%20this%20version%20they%20have%20been%20described%20as%20devotees%20of%20Ram.%20What%20relation%20they%20had%20with%20Ram%20and%20why%20they%20did%20not%20find%20mention%20anywhere%20else%20in%20the%20story%20is%20not%20known.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20members%20of%20this%20caste%20group%20have%20primarily%20depended%20on%20water.%20Since%20they%20did%20not%20have%20rights%20over%20land%2C%20they%20used%20water%20as%20the%20source%20of%20their%20livelihood.%20However%2C%20in%20many%20places%20in%20Bihar%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Odisha%2C%20they%20are%20also%20involved%20in%20agriculture.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20rivers%20are%20unable%20to%20sustain%20them%20any%20longer%20and%20they%20are%20forced%20to%20take%20up%20other%20occupations%20now.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20Bengal%20and%20Tripura%2C%20they%20make%20bamboo%20baskets%20and%20also%20work%20as%20labourers%20in%20tea%20gardens.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20now%20the%20process%20of%20Brahminising%20this%20caste%20group%2C%20which%20originally%20had%20a%20tribal%20culture%2C%20is%20almost%20complete.%20Most%20of%20the%20people%20of%20this%20caste%20do%20not%20consider%20themselves%20tribal%20any%20more.%20At%20some%20places%20they%20are%20Scheduled%20Castes.%20In%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Bihar%2C%20they%20have%20been%20linked%20to%20Ram%20while%20in%20Tripura%20they%20are%20associated%20with%20the%20Shaivite%20tradition.%20In%20Assam%2C%20they%20have%20been%20described%20as%20the%20followers%20of%20Vaishnav%20saint%20Shankaradev.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20addition%2C%20they%20have%20their%20own%20festivals%20and%20rituals.%20For%20instance%2C%20Vishahari%20Puja%20is%20a%20famous%20festival%20in%20Bihar%20and%20Chaurasa%20Devi%20is%20worshipped.%20It%20is%20believed%20that%20this%20goddess%20resides%20on%20a%20boat%20and%20saves%20people%20from%20drowning.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20Hindi%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%20Read%20the%20Hindi%20original%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F262743%2Fbihar-caste-survey-kevat-caste-society%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20earlier%20parts%20of%20the%20series%20on%20the%20following%20communities%20by%20clicking%20on%20their%20names%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-