ining-Maharashtra-%2540-Ashish-Kothari-copy.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20stayed%20two%20Union%20government%20orders%20of%20July%202021%20and%20January%202022%20granting%20ex-post%20facto%20clearance%20for%20projects%20across%20sectors%20without%20prior%20environmental%20approval%20mandated%20under%20the%20Environment%20Impact%20Assessment%20(EIA)%20notification%20of%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20division%20Bench%20of%20Justice%20B.R.%20Gavai%20and%20Justice%20Sandeep%20Mehta%20issued%20a%20notice%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20January%203%2C%20to%20the%20ministry%20of%20the%20environment%20and%20forests%20(MoEF)%20on%20the%20plea%20filed%20by%20NGO%20Vanashakti.%20%E2%80%9CIssue%20notice%20returnable%20in%20four%20weeks.%20Until%20further%20orders%20there%20shall%20be%20a%20stay%20of%20the%20office%20memorandum%20dated%20January%2020%2C%202022%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Bench%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fsc-stays-moefs-office-memorandum-on-ex-post-facto-environmental-clearance%2Farticle67701236.ece%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fsc-stays-moefs-office-memorandum-on-ex-post-facto-environmental-clearance%2Farticle67701236.ece%5C%22%3E%20The%20Hindu%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVanashakti%E2%80%99s%20counsel%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Gopal%20Sankaranarayanan%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20EIA%20mandates%20prior%20approval%20before%20the%20start%20of%20any%20activity%2C%20and%20allowing%20ex%20post%20facto%20environmental%20clearance%20is%20%E2%80%9Canathema%20to%20the%20Environment%20Protection%20Act%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESankaranarayanan%20argued%20further%20that%20the%20EIA%20notification%20of%202006%20mandates%20prior%20environment%20clearance%20for%20all%20projects%20and%20the%20problem%20began%20with%20an%20office%20memorandum%20of%202017%20which%20provided%20a%20six-month%20window%20for%20alleged%20violators%20to%20apply%20for%20post%20facto%20clearance.%20To%20further%20his%20case%2C%20Sankaranarayanan%20cited%20previous%20Supreme%20Court%20orders%20which%20sought%20to%20balance%20the%20twin%20goals%20of%20sustainable%20development%20and%20environmental%20protection%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnon-derogable%E2%80%9D%20requirement%20under%20the%20law%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fsc-stays-ex-post-facto-mining-clearance-without-prior-environmental-clearance-101704252518222.html%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Blatantly%20illegal%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20MoEFCC%E2%80%99s%20January%202022%20Office%20Memorandum%2C%20however%2C%20generalised%20post-facto%20environmental%20clearance%20to%20projects%20across%20the%20entire%20country.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20felt%20that%20it%20was%20completely%20illogical%20and%20illegal%2C%20blatantly%20illegal%2C%E2%80%9D%20Stalin%20D.%2C%20one%20of%20the%20directors%20of%20the%20Mumbai-based%20NGO%20Vanashakti%20which%20filed%20the%20petition%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%E2%80%9CHow%20can%20a%20police%20commissioner%20or%20a%20DG%20issue%20a%20set%20of%20guidelines%20that%20tells%20criminals%20how%20to%20escape%20the%20law%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%202017%20notification%20provided%20a%20six-month%20window%20to%20apply%20for%20environmental%20clearance%2C%20so%20another%20one%20opening%20up%20projects%20for%20post-facto%20clearances%20was%20unnecessary%2C%20Stalin%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CNow%20forget%20windows%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20opening%20everything%2C%20doors%2C%20windows%2C%20that%20lets%20everyone%20come%20in%20and%20go%20as%20they%20want%2C%E2%80%9D%20Stalin%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%E2%80%9CThat%20cannot%20happen.%20This%20government%20has%20been%20systematically%20dismantling%20every%20safeguard%20that%20is%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20environment%E2%80%A6as%20we%20have%20seen%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20Forest%20Conservation%20Act%20amendment%20as%20well%E2%80%A6It%20is%20an%20uphill%20battle%20for%20all%20of%20us%20who%20are%20fighting%20this%2C%20not%20just%20me.%20But%20we%20can%E2%80%99t%20say%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20fight%20it%2C%20history%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20judge%20us%20and%20say%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20do%20anything.%20Let%20the%20burden%20of%20guilt%20or%20inaction%20be%20on%20the%20people%20who%20were%20supposed%20to%20take%20action.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVanashakti%20had%20already%20challenged%20the%20post%20facto%20environmental%20clearance%20proposed%20for%20the%20notification%20pertaining%20to%20the%20rules%20applying%20to%20the%20coastal%20regulation%20zone%20and%20have%20received%20a%20stay%20order%20for%20that%2C%20Stalin%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20But%20the%20MoEFCC%E2%80%99s%20January%202022%20Office%20Memorandum%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20affecting%20the%20entire%20country%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20sit%20back%20and%20think%20that%20someone%20%5Belse%5D%20will%20do%20it%20%5Bcontest%20the%20notification%5D%E2%80%9D%2C%20Stalin%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20realised%20that%20unless%20we%20put%20some%20kind%20of%20stumbling%20block%20everything%20will%20go%20out%20of%20the%20window%E2%80%A6that%20there%20will%20be%20nothing%20left%20to%20save%2C%20it%20will%20be%20a%20futile%20battle%20all%20along%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Definitely%20a%20win%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20ordered%20a%20stay%20on%20the%20notifications%20based%20on%20their%20writ%20petition%20filed%20in%20October%20last%20year%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdefinitely%20a%20win%E2%80%9D%2C%20Stalin%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20this%20stay%20will%20hold%20across%20all%20sectors%20makes%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20impactful%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cimportant%E2%80%9D%20stay%20by%20the%20court%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20case%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20heard%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20what%20twists%20and%20turns%20are%20going%20to%20come%20up%20later%20on%2C%20what%20the%20government%20will%20say%E2%80%A6%5Bbut%5D%20at%20least%20the%20judges%20saw%20that%20there%20was%20something%20seriously%20wrong%20with%20the%20way%20this%20was%20being%20done%2C%E2%80%9D%20Stalin%20said.%20%E2%80%9CBecause%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20EIA%20notification%2C%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Cprior%20clearance%E2%80%9D%20has%20been%20used%20not%20once%20or%20twice%2C%20but%2032%20times.%20That%E2%80%99s%20how%20much%20it%20has%20been%20emphasised.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20guiding%20principle%20in%20environmental%20jurisprudence%20is%20the%20precautionary%20principle%20(which%20states%20that%20if%20any%20product%2C%20action%20or%20policy%20has%20potential%20to%20cause%20harm%20to%20the%20public%20or%20the%20environment%2C%20authorities%20should%20err%20on%20the%20side%20of%20caution%20and%20take%20precautions%20to%20protect%20the%20environment%20or%20people%20than%20implement%20such%20a%20product%2C%20action%20or%20policy).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20%5Bthe%20precautionary%20principle%5D%2C%20the%20fundamental%20foundation%2C%20cannot%20be%20thrown%20out%2C%E2%80%9D%20Stalin%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Should%20be%20struck%20down%20completely%E2%80%99%3A%20Jairam%20Ramesh%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECommenting%20on%20the%20SC%E2%80%99s%20order%20to%20stay%20the%20MoEFCC%E2%80%99s%20office%20memoranda%2C%20former%20union%20environment%20minister%20and%20Congress%20member%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cabsolutely%20atrocious%20Modi%20government%20decision%E2%80%9D%20should%20be%20%E2%80%9Cstruck%20down%20completely%E2%80%9D%2C%20in%20a%20tweet%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20January%2020%2C%202022%20Office%20Memorandum%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Environment%2C%20Forests%20and%20Climate%20Change%2C%20allowing%20for%20environmental%20approvals%20AFTER%20a%20project%20had%20commenced%20was%20a%20disaster%20that%20had%20been%20foretold%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FJairam_Ramesh%2Fstatus%2F1742589346048508023%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etweeted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20only%20a%20partial%20relief%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20now%20put%20that%20absolutely%20atrocious%20Modi%20government%20decision%20on%20hold.%20The%20decision%20should%20actually%20be%20struck%20down%20completely.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20An%20earlier%20version%20of%20this%20article%20had%20mentioned%2C%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20initial%20reports%2C%20that%20the%20stay%20was%20on%20mining%20projects%20alone.%20It%20is%20across%20all%20sectors%2C%20sources%20have%20told%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704279644000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F04%2F15182007%2FCoal-mining-Maharashtra-%2540-Ashish-Kothari-copy.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-stays-centres-orders-on-ex-post-facto-environmental-clearance-for-mining-projects%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20imposed%20a%20stay%20on%20MoEF's%20July%202021%20and%20January%202022%20orders%2C%20which%20granted%20permission%20for%20ex-post%20facto%20clearance%20without%20prior%20approval%20mandated%20under%20the%20Environment%20Impact%20Assessment%20notification%20of%202006.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-stays-centres-orders-on-ex-post-facto-environmental-clearance-for-mining-projects%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20Jurisprudence%20Seems%20to%20Be%20Bending%20to%20the%20Will%20of%20Hindutva%20Forces%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F22141813%2Fnalsar-final.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20Modi-%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eyug%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(era)%2C%20where%20Hindutva%20Brahmanical%20majoritarianism%20is%20subverting%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20by%20reinterpretation%20and%20distortion%2C%20the%20unanimous%20verdict%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20constitutional%20bench%20upholding%20the%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370%20and%20the%20convoluted%20logic%20it%20offers%20to%20justify%20its%20concurrence%20with%20the%20political%20acts%20of%20Modi%20should%20be%20a%20matter%20of%20great%20concern%20to%20people%20who%20care%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20future%20as%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esecular%2C%20democratic%20and%20federal%20republic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20if%20the%20similarity%20of%20the%20judicial%20logic%20and%20other%20self%20contradictory%20judicial%20premises%20that%20the%20top%20court%20offered%20in%20the%20Ayodhya%20judgement%20%E2%80%93%20another%20political%20agenda%20central%20to%20the%20Hindutva%20right%20%E2%80%93%20is%20considered%2C%20the%20questions%20become%20more%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efundamental%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20benches%20that%20adjudicated%20the%20Article%20370%20case%20and%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20case%20were%20constitutional%20benches%20of%20five%20judges%20led%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%2C%20then%20and%20now.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20bench%20in%20both%20the%20cases%20consisted%20of%20the%20senior%20most%20in%20the%20apex%20court%20who%20were%20in%20line%20to%20become%20CJIs%20except%20for%20Justice%20N.V.%20Ramana%20in%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20dispute.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20the%20cases%20were%20of%20utmost%20importance%20to%20the%20ideological%20project%20of%20Hindu%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERashtra%20(nation)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20present%20regime.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20both%20the%20cases%2C%20the%20Hindutva%20forces%20had%20achieved%20their%20goals%20partially%20and%20in%20a%20de-facto%20manner%2C%20the%20judicial%20verdicts%20gave%20them%20a%20final%20and%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ede%20jure%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20closure%20in%20their%20favour.%20Through%20these%20verdicts%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20normalised%20the%20most%20abnormal%20and%20constitutionalised%20the%20most%20unconstitutional%20while%20providing%20judicial%20legitimacy%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20Hindu%20Rashtra.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%2C%20in%20both%20the%20cases%2C%20the%20bench%20constituted%20the%20cream%20of%20the%20Indian%20judiciary%20and%20the%20verdict%20was%20unanimous%2C%20their%20judgements%20cannot%20be%20considered%20either%20as%20an%20aberration%20or%20exceptional.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Findia-democracy-statue-manu-ambedkar%5C%22%3EIn%20Democratic%20India%2C%20Why%20Was%20Statue%20of%20Manu%20Installed%20in%20a%20Court%20Before%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%20the%20CJI%2C%20in%20an%20interview%20to%20PTI%20has%20said%20that%20in%20the%20Ayodhya%20case%2C%20the%20anonymity%20and%20unanimity%20of%20the%20judgement%20was%20conscious%20so%20that%20a%20strong%20message%20of%20complete%20judicial%20concurrence%20in%20the%20rationale%20and%20the%20judgement%20is%20conveyed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHence%20the%20critique%20of%20these%20judgements%20should%20also%20raise%20some%20very%20fundamental%20questions%20pertaining%20to%20the%20character%20and%20direction%20the%20Indian%20jurisprudence%20is%20heading%20towards.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20a%20closer%20analysis%20of%20both%20the%20judgements%20indicates%20the%20dangerous%20emergence%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20majoritarian%20jurisprudence%20in%20direct%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eproportion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20the%20majoritarian%20polity%20ruling%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETake%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20judgement%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eon%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370%20and%20bifurcation%20of%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAbrogation%20of%20Article%20370%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EArticle%20370%20was%20a%20manifest%20instrument%20of%20guarantee%20of%20the%20autonomy%20and%20limited%20sovereignty%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eassured%20by%20the%20Indian%20constitution%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20even%20after%20its%20accession%20to%20Indian%20republic.%20While%20the%20erstwhile%20governments%2C%20including%20the%20Congress%2C%20had%20been%20betraying%20the%20guarantee%20surreptitiously%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20and%20its%20previous%20avatar%2C%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%2C%20wanted%20a%20blatant%2C%20forcible%20and%20complete%20integration%20of%20the%20predominantly%20a%20Muslim%20state%20into%20Indian%20Union.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThus%2C%20after%20the%20Modi%20government%20came%20to%20power%20for%20the%20second%20time%20in%202019%2C%20on%20a%20Hindu%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERashtra%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eagenda%2C%20it%20abrogated%20Article%20370%20through%20presidential%20orders.%20The%20question%20before%20the%20constitutional%20bench%20was%20the%20illegality%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eirrationality%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20procedural%20impropriety%20and%20constitutional%20immorality%20involved%20in%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20act.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F04140855%2FFz4IkQzakAQFUBj.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221132%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F04140855%2FFz4IkQzakAQFUBj.jpeg%201132w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F04140855%2FFz4IkQzakAQFUBj-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F04140855%2FFz4IkQzakAQFUBj-1024x682.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-661553%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22754%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20and%20other%20judges%20at%20an%20event%20in%20Srinagar%20last%20week.%20On%20the%20right%20is%20J%26amp%3BK%20lieutenant%20governor%20Manoj%20Sinha.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40OfficeOfLGJandK%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20senior%20legal%20luminaries%20like%20Justice%20(retired)%20Madan%20Lokur%2C%20Justice%20(retired)%20Rohinton%20Nariman%20and%20constitutional%20experts%20like%20Fali%20Nariman%20and%20many%20such%20sane%20voices%20in%20the%20legal%20world%20have%20already%20exposed%20many%20serious%20constitutional%20flaws%20in%20the%20judgement%20which%20could%20be%20summarised%20as%20being%20arbitrary%20at%20the%20best%20or%20preconceived%20at%20worst.%20They%20are%20surprised%20at%20the%20reluctance%20of%20the%20bench%20in%20examining%20the%20constitutional%20validity%20of%20the%20degradation%20of%20the%20status%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20also%20at%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eeagerness%20of%20the%20bench%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20be%20legally%20satisfied%20by%20oral%20promise%20of%20the%20executive%20to%20restore%20the%20status%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Estatehood%20to%20Kashmir%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20They%20also%20found%20it%20unconvincing%2C%20the%20Bench%E2%80%99s%20approval%20to%20the%20postponement%20of%20elections%20till%20after%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections!%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20premise%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20in%20upholding%20the%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370%20smacks%20of%20selective%20reading%20of%20its%20insertion%20as%20a%20temporary%20measure%20completely%20in%20tune%20with%20the%20distorted%20arguments%20of%20RSS-BJP%20which%20considers%20Article%20370%20as%20a%20constitutional%20impediment.%20In%20fact%20CJI%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20judgement%20goes%20to%20an%20extent%20of%20declaring%20that%3A%20%E2%80%9CJammu%20and%20Kashmir%20did%20not%20retain%20any%20sovereignty%20after%20accession%20to%20India%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20interpretation%20goes%20against%20the%20explanation%20given%20by%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20in%20the%20Constitutional%20Assembly%20about%20the%20residual%20sovereignty%20of%20the%20states%20and%20sets%20a%20dangerous%20precedent%20for%20other%20states%20in%20the%20republic.%20According%20to%20Ambedkar%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6a%20dual%20polity%20consisting%20of%20the%20Union%20at%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20states%20at%20the%20periphery%2C%20each%20endowed%20with%20sovereign%20powers%20to%20be%20exercised%20in%20the%20field%20assigned%20to%20them%20respectively%20by%20the%20Constitution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20the%20convoluted%20logic%20provided%20by%20the%20constitutional%20bench%20in%20establishing%20the%20temporariness%20of%20Article%20370%20relies%20on%20a%20peripheral%20fact%20of%20its%20inclusion%20in%20the%20constitutional%20lists%20dealing%20with%20the%20temporary%20measures%20and%20not%20on%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esubstantial%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20debates%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20or%20the%20constitutional%20history%20leading%20to%20the%20Article%20370%20as%20instrument%20of%20constitutional%20guarantee.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20most%20questionable%20part%20of%20the%20judgement%20regarding%20abrogation%20of%20the%20Article%20370%20is%20its%20very%20illogical%20reading%20of%20the%20meaning%20of%20370%20(3).%20According%20to%20this%20clause%2C%20a%20recommendation%20from%20the%20constitutional%20assembly%20of%20Kashmir%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnecessary%E2%80%9D%20precondition%20for%20the%20President%20of%20India%20before%20he%20ordered%20its%20abrogation.%20But%20the%20learned%20judges%20have%20wilfully%20neglected%20the%20conditionality%20provided%20in%20the%20clause.%20They%20wishfully%20read%20it%20as%20either%20of%20one%2C%20and%20read%20down%20the%20necessary%20precondition%20of%20concurrence%20of%20the%20constituent%20assembly%20of%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Flooking-beyond-politics-constitution-and-law-how-the-people-of-jk-feel-about-scs-decision%5C%22%3ELooking%20Beyond%20Politics%2C%20Constitution%20and%20Law%3A%20How%20the%20People%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20Feel%20About%20SC%E2%80%99s%20Decision%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20bench%20considers%20the%20hitherto%20extensions%20of%20the%20Indian%20statutes%20to%20Kashmir%20by%20erstwhile%20governments%20as%20a%20sufficient%20condition%20to%20abrogate%20the%20Article%20370.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECJI%20Chandrachud%20reasonably%20found%20fault%20with%20the%20way%20Article%20368%20is%20used%20to%20amend%20Article%20370%20(3)%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20substituting%20the%20terms%20%E2%80%9Clegislative%20assembly%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20place%20of%20%E2%80%9CConstitutional%20assembly%E2%80%9D%20and%20thereby%20acquiring%20constitutional%20authority%20to%20abrogate%20Article%20370.%20Even%20though%20the%20CJI%20considers%20this%20process%20as%20unconstitutional%20and%20strikes%20it%20down%2C%20the%20bench%20does%20not%20consider%20the%20act%20of%20abrogation%2C%20made%20through%20this%20faulty%20constitutional%20process%2C%20as%20wrong.%20This%20is%20surprising%20and%20appears%20intentional%20because%20the%20hitherto%20jurisprudence%20considered%20procedural%20propriety%20as%20sacrosanct%20and%20equal%20to%20the%20intent%20of%20the%20law.%20It%20held%20that%20an%20act%20brought%20through%20improper%20procedure%20is%20null%20and%20void!%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAyodhya%20judgement%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20may%20appear%20less%20surprising%20when%20the%20Ayodhya%20judgement%20%E2%80%93%20where%20similar%20illogical%20and%20contradictory%20arguments%20are%20provided%20to%20uphold%20the%20claim%20on%20the%20land%20where%20Babri%20Masjid%20existed%20%E2%80%93%20is%20analysed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20course%20of%20the%20Ayodhya%20judgement%2C%20the%20constitutional%20bench%20had%20declared%20that%20there%20is%20no%20proof%20to%20suggest%20a%20temple%20existed%20beneath%20the%20mosque%20while%20concluding%20that%20Babri%20Masjid%E2%80%99s%20destruction%20was%20an%20egregious%20crime.%20Still%2C%20it%20came%20to%20a%20strange%20conclusion%20contrary%20to%20its%20own%20reasoning%20by%20privileging%20the%20faith%20and%20belief%20of%20the%20majority%20over%20the%20facts%20and%20the%20evidence%20provided%20by%20the%20minority.%20Thus%20the%20bench%20reasoned%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6Matters%20of%20faith%20and%20belief%20lie%20in%20the%20personal%20realm%20of%20the%20believer.%20That%20which%20sustains%20solace%20to%20the%20soul%20is%20inscrutable.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EWhether%20a%20belief%20is%20justified%20lies%20beyond%20ken%20of%20judicial%20inquiry%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20This%20is%20not%20a%20case%20where%20the%20witness%20statements%20indicate%20that%20the%20belief%20or%20faith%20is%20a%20veneer%20or%20that%20it%20is%20being%20put-forth%20merely%20as%20a%20strategy%20in%20a%20litigation.%20Once%20the%20witnesses%20have%20deposed%20to%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20belief%20and%20there%20is%20nothing%20to%20doubt%20its%20genuineness%2C%20it%20is%20not%20open%20to%20the%20court%20to%20question%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20belief.%20Scriptural%20interpretations%20are%20susceptible%20to%20a%20multitude%20of%20inferences.%20The%20court%20would%20do%20well%20not%20to%20step%20into%20the%20pulpit%20by%20adjudging%20which%2C%20if%20any%2C%20of%20competing%20interpretations%20should%20be%20accepted.%20Faith%20is%20a%20matter%20for%20the%20individual%20believer.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-ram-temple-at-ayodhya-is-a-symbol-of-injustice-congress-leaders-should-stay-away-from-it%5C%22%3EThe%20Ram%20Temple%20at%20Ayodhya%20is%20a%20Symbol%20of%20Injustice%2C%20Congress%20Leaders%20Should%20Stay%20Away%20from%20It%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThus%2C%20the%20whole%20judgement%20was%20based%20on%20deferring%20to%20the%20faith%20of%20the%20Hindus%20rather%20than%20the%20bundles%20of%20proof%20and%20evidence%20provided%20by%20the%20Muslim%20petitioners.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20trend%20in%20the%20judiciary%20becomes%20more%20apparent%20if%20one%20compares%20how%20the%20faith%20of%20the%20Hindu%20believer%20is%20allowed%20in%20the%20Ayodhya%20judgement%20but%20denied%20to%20Muslims%20in%20the%20Hijab%20judgement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20three%20judge%20bench%20of%20Karnataka%20high%20court%20on%20hijab%20ban%20declared%20that%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6Conscience%20is%20by%20its%20very%20nature%20subjective.%20Whether%20the%20petitioners%20had%20the%20conscience%20of%20the%20kind%20and%20how%20they%20developed%20it%20are%20not%20averred%20in%20the%20petition%20with%20material%20particulars.%20Merely%20stating%20that%20wearing%20hijab%20is%20an%20overt%20act%20of%20conscience%20and%20therefore%2C%20asking%20them%20to%20remove%20hijab%20would%20offend%20conscience%2C%20would%20not%20be%20sufficient%20for%20treating%20it%20as%20a%20ground%20for%20granting%20relief%E2%80%A6%20No%20material%20is%20placed%20before%20us%20for%20evaluation%20and%20determination%20of%20pleaded%20conscience%20of%20the%20petitioners.%20They%20have%20not%20averred%20anything%20as%20to%20how%20they%20associate%20wearing%20hijab%20with%20their%20conscience%2C%20as%20an%20overt%20act.%20There%20is%20no%20evidence%20that%20the%20petitioners%20chose%20to%20wear%20their%20headscarf%20as%20a%20means%20of%20conveying%20any%20thought%20or%20belief%20on%20their%20part%20or%20as%20a%20means%20of%20symbolic%20expression.%20Pleadings%20at%20least%20for%20urging%20the%20ground%20of%20conscience%20are%20perfunctory%2C%20to%20say%20the%20least.%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20judgement%20is%20guided%20by%20the%20Ayodhya%20judgement%20for%20its%20rationale.%20Thus%20it%20quotes%3A%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C..The%20Constitution%20Bench%20of%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%2C%20in%20M.Siddique%20Vs.%20Mahanth%20Suresh%20Das%2C%20the%20Ram%20Janma%20Bhumi%20Temple%20case%20has%20held%20that%20faith%20is%20a%20matter%20for%20the%20individual%20believer.%20Once%20the%20Court%20has%20intrinsic%20material%20to%20accept%20that%20the%20faith%20or%20belief%20is%20genuine%2C%20it%20must%20defer%20to%20the%20belief%20of%20the%20worshipper.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENot%20only%20this%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20in%20the%20Ayodhya%20judgement%2C%20extolled%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%201991%2C%20which%20bars%20the%20conversion%20of%20the%20religious%20nature%20of%20the%20historical%20religious%20shrines%2C%20as%20an%20instrument%20of%20safeguarding%20the%20secular%20fabric%20of%20India.%20But%20Justice%20Chandrachud%2C%20after%20becoming%20the%20CJI%2C%20has%20allowed%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20same%20act.%20The%20bench%20led%20by%20him%20has%20also%20diluted%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%201991%20Act%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20and%20Mathura%20Masjid%20cases%2C%20arguing%20that%20ascertaining%20the%20religious%20nature%20of%20the%20disputed%20shrines%20is%20not%20prohibited%20under%20the%201991%20act.%20The%20Hindutva%20forces%20are%20celebrating%20the%20same%20as%20judicial%20endorsement%20of%20their%20agenda.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThus%2C%20the%20similarities%20of%20these%20judgements%2C%20which%20concur%20with%20the%20Hindutva%20agenda%2C%20do%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20accidental%20or%20coincidental.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EShivasundar%20is%20an%20activist%20and%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20based%20in%20Bangalore.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704277816000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F22141813%2Fnalsar-final.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Findian-jurisprudence-seems-to-be-bending-to-the-will-of-hindutva-forces%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20closer%20analysis%20of%20key%20Supreme%20Court%20judgements%20indicates%20the%20dangerous%20emergence%20